The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 25: The government will amend rules to allow units in SEZs to use old machinery and still qualify for tax concessions. Earlier, it had prohibited use of second hand machinery in SEZs to prevent migration of units from domestic tariff area to the tax free zones. The changes in the act will be notified in the next three to four weeks.

 New Delhi, July 25: The railways have reduced the service charges for sleeper class to Rs 10 from Rs 15 since July 1 this year to encourage e-ticket usage. However, additional charges will remain the same.

 New Delhi, July 25: Punjab National Bank has posted a 15.66 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 425.07 crore for the first quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 367.52 crore a year ago. Total income grew to Rs 3,795.12 crore from Rs 2,923.2 crore.

 New Delhi, July 25: The BSNL employees union, assured by telecom minister A. Raja of a fresh tender for 90 million mobile lines, today deferred a decision on striking work till the first week of September.

 New Delhi, Jul 25: Pfizer Inc has said a Spanish Court has upheld its enantiomer patent covering calcium salt of atorvastatin against generic manufacturer Ranbaxy.




